230.description:
Sat, 27 Oct 2012 00:17:23 +0800
Dozens killed in suicide bomb attack 
 At least 41 people were killed and dozens wounded when a suicide bomber struck at a mosque in Maymana city in northern Afghanistan during Eid al-Adha prayers on Friday.A local official said the attacker wore a police uniform when he blew himself up in the crowded Eid Gah mosque.Several children were said to be among the dead.
